title: Independent Candidate Pakhtun Yar Khan wins PK-100 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Pakhtun Yar Khan won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-100, Bannu-II by securing 30,925 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Akram Khan Durrani who bagged 23,909 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 39.98 percent.
